description.narrative: UNICEF continued to generate evidence to inform policy design and effective programming in Jordan. Accurate data is critical to develop programmes that address equity gaps and structural system challenges and help deliver critical services for the most vulnerable and marginalized populations in Jordan. UNICEF continued its efforts to upraise original data as part of the multi-agency collaboration and assessed dietary diversity and the nutritional status of pre-school and school-aged children as well as women in reproductive age in Jordan.;Additionally, UNICEF worked with USAID’s Community Health and Nutrition programme to support updating the national nutrition strategy. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:12/01/2022
